          "updated_at": "2026-02-21T18:45:10Z",
          "body": "Related: #22170 proposes Cordum as an external safety backend that complements this. Where this issue focuses on sandbox/session isolation at the runtime level, Cordum adds a policy evaluation layer *before* execution — the safety kernel evaluates every tool call against configurable policies (deny, escalate, allow) with per-tenant, per-agent scoping. Defense in depth: OpenClaw sandboxes the runtime, Cordum gates what's allowed to run in the first place.",
